<DocsLayout title="Quick Start" headings={headings}>
    <h1 id="quick-start">Quick Start</h1>

    <p>Create a minimal Newgate API in seconds.</p>

    <h2 id="1-initialize-project">1. Initialize Project</h2>

    <p>Create a new directory and initialize your project:</p>

    <pre><code class="language-bash">mkdir my-newgate-app
cd my-newgate-app
npm init -y
npm install newgatejs
</code></pre>

    <h2 id="2-create-server">2. Create Server</h2>

    <p>
        Create a file named <code>server.js</code> with the following content:
    </p>

    <pre><code class="language-javascript">import App from 'newgatejs';

const app = new App();

// Basic route
app.get('/', (req, res) =&gt; &#123;
    res.json(&#123; message: "Hello from Newgate!" &#125;);
&#125;);

// Start server
app.listen(3000, () =&gt; &#123;
    console.log('Server running at http://localhost:3000');
&#125;);
</code></pre>

    <h2 id="3-run">3. Run</h2>

    <p>Start your server:</p>

    <pre><code class="language-bash">node server.js
</code></pre>

    <h2 id="4-test">4. Test</h2>

    <p>Open another terminal and test your endpoint:</p>

    <pre><code class="language-bash">curl http://localhost:3000
# Output: &#123;"message":"Hello from Newgate!"&#125;
</code></pre>
